sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ChlOp2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This operon codes for protochlorophyllide when combined with BBa_K1080026, on the synthetic pathway to chlorophyll.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Macquarie University

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K864400
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The Ptac promoter is a functional hybrid promoter, derived from the trp and lac promoters, that are regulated by trp and lac [1]. This part also exist together with lacI, part [[Part:BBa_K180000|BBa_K180000]]
[1] Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, Vol. 80, pp. 21-25
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Lundin
